data.description: Charming craftsman style bungalow near Irvingdale park; classic character with updates throughout. Refinished hardwood floors, updated kitchen & bathroom, beautiful custom coffered/beamed ceiling in formal dining, all new lighting & electrical trims, updated electric panel, mostly newer wiring, fresh paint. And something rarely found in homes of this age…the primary bed has an attached full bath. We’re not kidding. 3 beds on the main floor or 2 plus a bonus room/office/den. Unfinished attic with stairway could be finished for more living space, and the basement is unfinished but has a 3/4 bathroom. Awesome outdoor space, too! A large enclosed front porch, 4 raised garden beds, perennial landscaping including strawberries, peonies, yellow roses, hostas, and an oversized 2.5 stall detached garage. Great opportunity to own a solid turn of the century home in a great neighborhood, for a fraction of the price of less updated homes in the area. Security system does not stay with the house.
